Doc Spatz,<br>
     OK, so they talk, and have been doing so for years.  Would you rather they all shot each other? (No show of hands please!)  Freedom of the press gives the right of the media to broadcast or publish anything it finds out about the proceedings, but doesn't take away the rights of the participants to keep their discussions private, whether they're talking about Hillary's chances of being indicted or  whose horse to back in the play for Central Asian oil.  For one thing; there's too many people involved over the years for any conspiracy not to spring a dozen leaks.  That doesn't mean that all the talking won't lead to some really dumb decisions by somebody.  There's human beings involved, and as Ish Kabibble used to say, &quot;Humans are the craziest peoples&quot;, the rich and famous not excepted.                            
